<h1>Music</h1>

<div class="columns">

  <div class="column column--left animate__animated animate__fadeInLeftBig">

    <p>I’ve been making music for over 25 years. I cut my teeth whilst at art school, writing and performing my brooding confessional elegies on the London open mic circuit. I went on to self-produce many solo albums and EPs, as well as gigging and recording with the bands Bird Bones, Boo Forever, and <a href="https://www.instagram.com/_forestfloor_/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="This is an external link (opens in a new tab)">forestfloor</a>, spanning genres such as Sadcore, Post-Rock, Indie, Folktronica, and Alt Hip-hop.</p>

    <p>In recent years I’ve returned to the guitar with a beginner’s mindset, exploring metal chugging, country chicken pickin’, swampy bottleneck slide, and other styles outside my comfort zone, purely for the pleasure of learning.</p>

    <p>You can access a small selection of my music on <a href="https://danaddison.bandcamp.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="This is an external link (opens in a new tab)">BandCamp</a>, or on <a href="https://soundcloud.com/danaddison" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="This is an external link (opens in a new tab)">SoundCloud</a>, and most of my lyrics can be found in my <a href="https://lyrics.danaddison.uk" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="This is an external link (opens in a new tab)">online archive.</a></p>

